9 An Act relating to bail; amending 22 O.S. 2021,
Section 1077, which relates to bail allowable on
10 appeal; prohibiting bail on appeal for certain
offenses; updating statutory language; updating
11 statutory reference; and providing an effective date.
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 22 O.S. 2021, Section 1077, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 1077. Bail on appeal shall be allowed on appeal from a
17 judgment of conviction of a misdemeanor, or in felony cases where
18 the punishment is a fine only, and when made and approved shall stay
19 the execution of such judgment. Bail on appeal after the effective
20 date of this act April 17, 1969, shall not be allowed after
21 conviction of any of the following offenses:
22 1. Murder in any degree;
23 2. Kidnapping for purpose of extortion;
24 3. Robbery with a dangerous weapon;
Req. No. 1982 Page 1

1 4. Rape in any degree;
2 5. Arson in the first degree;
3 6. Shooting with intent to kill;
4 7. Manslaughter in the first degree;
5 8. Forcible sodomy;
6 9. Any felony conviction for which the evidence shows that the
7 defendant used or was in possession of a firearm or other dangerous
8 or deadly weapon during the commission of the offense;
9 10. Trafficking in illegal drugs;
10 11. Manufacturing a controlled dangerous substance;
11 12. Abuse against an intimate partner as defined by Section
12 60.1 of this title;
13 13. Abuse of a child;
14 14. Sexual abuse of a child; or
15 13. 15. Any other felony after former conviction of a felony.
16 The granting or refusal of bail after judgment of conviction in
17 all other felony cases shall rest in the discretion of the court;
18 provided, however, if bail is allowed, the trial court shall state
19 the reason therefor for granting bail.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
